      <text>Effect of Depth of Field and Astigmatism on Holographic Image Clarity</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>In a rainbow holographic display, a hologram is viewed from a distance of <span class="math-tex">\(D_{view} = 600 \, mm\)</span>. The maximum allowable astigmatism is set to <span class="math-tex">\(0.2 \, diopters\)</span>. Determine the allowable range of depth of field (both in front of and behind the hologram) before image clarity is significantly affected by astigmatism.

Use the relationships:
<span class="math-tex">\(A_1 = \frac{1}{D_{view}} - \frac{1}{D_{front}}\)</span> and <span class="math-tex">\(A_2 = \frac{1}{D_{back}} - \frac{1}{D_{view}}\)</span>,
where <span class="math-tex">\(A_1\)</span> and <span class="math-tex">\(A_2\)</span> represent the allowable astigmatism limits.<img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/hh.images/FIG-DOF-ASTIG-0002.png" width="400" /></p>]]></text>
